column10: Yellow & red interval is too short for people walking and on bicycles to clear the intersection.  Right hand turning drivers jumped the green and harassed a person on a bike completing the crosswalk northbound and a family on bikes cutoff from entering the crosswalk southbound.
column21: Drivers from behind the first in the queue don't look for people walking or on bikes after the first one in the queue has gone right on red and jumped the green.
